33\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The sons of the servants of Solomon: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Sophereth, the sons of Perida, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 58}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 59}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth-hazzebaim, the sons of Amon. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 60}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?All the temple servants}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and the sons of the servants of Solomon were 392.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 61}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And these went up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addon, and Immer, but they were unable to verify their paternal house and their origin, as to whether they were Israelites: }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 62}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, 642. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 63}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And of the priests: the sons of Habaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, the sons of Barzillai, who took a wife from the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite and was called by their name. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 64}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?These looked for their records to establish their genealogy, but they could not be found, so they were disqualified from the priesthood.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 65}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The governor}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  told them that they should not eat from the most holy things until there was a priest who could consult the Urim and Thummim.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 66}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The total number of the entire congregation was 42,360, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 67}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?apart from their male and female slaves, who were 7,337; they also had 245 male and female singers. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 68}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Their horses were 736, their mules 245, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 69}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?their camels 435, their donkeys 6,720.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 70}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Some of the heads of the paternal houses contributed to the work. The governor}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  gave to the treasury 1,000 gold drachmas,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  50 bowls, and 530 priests\u8217? robes. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 71}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And some of the heads of the paternal houses gave to the project treasury 20,000 gold drachmas and 2,200 silver minas.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 72}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And the rest of the people gave 20,000 gold drachmas, 2,000 silver minas, and 67 priests\u8217? robes.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 73}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of the people, the temple servants,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and all the rest of Israel}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  settled in their cities. When the seventh month arrived, the Israelites had settled in their cities.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf5\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf7 8\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?All the people then gathered with one accord at the public square in front of the Water Gate, and they told Ezra the copyist}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  to bring the book of the Law of Moses, which Jehovah had commanded Israel. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?So Ezra the priest brought the Law before the congregation of men, women, and all who could listen with understanding, on the first day of the seventh month. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And he read aloud from it before the public square in front of the Water Gate, from daybreak until midday, to the men, the women, and all who could understand; and the people listened attentively to the book of the Law. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And Ezra the copyist}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  was standing on a wooden podium made for the occasion; and standing alongside him on his right were Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah; and on his left were Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum, Hash-baddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, for he was above all the people. As he opened it, all the people stood up. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Then Ezra praised Jehovah the true God, the great One, at which all the people answered, \u8220?Amen!}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  Amen!\u8221? and lifted up their hands. They then bowed low and prostrated themselves to Jehovah with their faces to the ground. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, and Pelaiah, who were Levites, were explaining the Law to the people, while the people remained standing. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And they continued reading aloud from the book, from the Law of the true God, clearly explaining it and putting meaning into it; so they helped the people to understand what was being read.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And Nehemiah, who was then the governor,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  Ezra the priest and copyist,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and the Levites who were instructing the people said to all the people: \u8220?This day is holy to Jehovah your God. Do not mourn or weep.\u8221? For all the people were weeping as they heard the words of the Law. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?He said to them: \u8220?Go, eat the choice things}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and drink what is sweet, and send portions of food to those who have nothing prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord, and do not feel sad, for the joy of Jehovah is your stronghold.\u8221?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And the Levites were calming all the people, saying: \u8220?Be quiet! for this day is holy, and do not feel sad.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?So all the people went away to eat and to drink and to send out portions of food and to carry on a great rejoicing, for they understood the words that had been made known to them.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And on the second day, the heads of the paternal houses of all the people, the priests, and the Levites gathered around Ezra the copyist}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  to gain further insight into the words of the Law. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Then they found written in the Law that Jehovah had commanded through Moses that the Israelites should dwell in booths}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  during the festival in the seventh month, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and that they should make proclamation and announce throughout all their cities and throughout Jerusalem, saying: \u8220?Go out to the mountainous region and bring in leafy branches from olive trees, pine trees, myrtle and palm trees, and the leafy branches of other trees to make booths, according to what is written.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?So the people went out and brought them in to make booths for themselves, each one on his roof, as well as in their courtyards, in the courtyards of the house of the true God, in the public square of the Water Gate, and in the public square of the Gate of Ephraim. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Thus all those of the congregation who had come back from the captivity made booths and were dwelling in the booths, for the Israelites had not done it this way from the days of Joshua the son of Nun until that day, so that there was very great rejoicing. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And day by day there was a reading from the book of the Law of the true God, from the first day until the last day. And they held the festival for seven days, and there was a solemn assembly on the eighth day, as was required.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf5\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf7 9\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?On the 24th day of this month the Israelites assembled; they were fasting with sackcloth and dust on themselves. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Those of Israelite descent then separated themselves from all the foreigners, and they stood and confessed their own sins and the errors of their fathers. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Then they stood up at their place and read aloud from the book of the Law of Jehovah their God for a fourth of the day;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and for another fourth of it they were confessing and bowing down to Jehovah their God.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani stood on the raised platform of the Levites, and they cried out with a loud voice to Jehovah their God. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And the Levites Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah said: \u8220?Stand up and praise Jehovah your God throughout all eternity.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  And let them praise your glorious name, which is exalted above all blessing and praise.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?You alone are Jehovah; you made the heavens, yes, the heaven of the heavens and all their army, the earth and all that is on it, the seas and all that is in them. And you preserve all of them alive, and the army of the heavens are bowing down to you. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You are Jehovah the true God, who chose Abram and brought him out of Ur of the Chaldeans and gave him the name Abraham. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You found his heart faithful before you, so you made a covenant with him to give him the land of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Jebusites, and the Girgashites, to give it to his offspring;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and you kept your promises, because you are righteous.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?So you saw the affliction of our forefathers in Egypt, and you heard their outcry at the Red Sea. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Then you performed signs and miracles against Pharaoh and all his servants and all the people of his land, for you knew that they acted presumptuously against them. You made a name for yourself that remains to this day. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And you split the sea before them, so that they crossed through the sea on the dry land, and you hurled their pursuers into the depths like a stone thrown into the turbulent waters. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You led them by day with a pillar of cloud, and by night with a pillar of fire, to light up for them the way they should go. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And you came down on Mount Sinai and spoke with them from heaven and gave them righteous judgments, laws of truth,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  good regulations and commandments. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You made known to them your holy Sabbath, and you gave them commandments, regulations, and a law through your servant Moses. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You gave them bread from heaven when they were hungry, and you brought water out of the crag when they were thirsty, and you told them to enter and take possession of the land that you had sworn}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  to give to them.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?But they, our forefathers, acted presumptuously and became stubborn,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and they would not listen to your commandments. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?They refused to listen, and they did not remember your extraordinary acts that you performed among them, but they became stubborn}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and appointed a head to return to their slavery in Egypt. But you are a God ready to forgive,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  compassionate}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and merciful, slow to anger and abundant in loyal love,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and you did not abandon them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Even when they made for themselves a metal statue}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  of a calf and were saying, \u8216?This is your God who led you up out of Egypt,\u8217? and they committed great acts of disrespect, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?even then you, in your great mercy, did not abandon them in the wilderness. The pillar of cloud did not depart from over them by day to lead them in the way, nor the pillar of fire by night to light up for them the way they should go. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And you gave your good spirit to give them insight, and you did not hold back your manna from their mouth, and you gave them water when they were thirsty. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?For 40 years you provided them with food in the wilderness. They lacked nothing. Their garments did not wear out, and their feet did not become swollen.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?You gave them kingdoms and peoples, apportioning them piece by piece, so that they took possession of the land of Sihon, that is, the land of the king of Heshbon, as well as the land of Og the king of Bashan. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And you made their sons as numerous as the stars of the heavens. Then you brought them into the land that you had promised their forefathers that they should enter and possess. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?So their sons went in and took possession of the land, and you subdued before them the Canaanites, who were the inhabitants of the land, and you gave them into their hand, both their kings and the peoples of the land, to do with them as they pleased. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And they captured fortified cities and a fertile}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  land, and they took possession of houses full of all sorts of good things, cisterns already dug, vineyards, olive groves, and fruit trees in abundance. So they ate and grew satisfied and fat, and they basked in your great goodness.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 26}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?However, they became disobedient and rebelled against you and turned their back on your Law.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  They killed your prophets who warned them so as to bring them back to you, and they committed acts of great disrespect. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 27}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?For this you gave them into the hand of their adversaries, who kept causing them distress. But they would cry out to you in the time of their distress, and you would hear from the heavens; and because of your great mercy, you would give them saviors to rescue them out of the hand of their adversaries.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 28}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?But as soon as they had relief, they would again do what is bad before you, and you would abandon them to the hand of their enemies, who would dominate them.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  Then they would return and call to you for help, and you would hear from the heavens and rescue them time and again because of your great mercy. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 29}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Although you would warn them so as to bring them back to your Law, they behaved presumptuously and refused to listen to your commandments; and they sinned against your regulations, by which a man will live if he observes them. But they stubbornly turned their back and stiffened their neck, and they refused to listen. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 30}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You extended patience to them for many years and kept warning them by your spirit through your prophets, but they refused to listen. Finally you gave them into the hand of the peoples of the lands. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 31}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And in your great mercy, you did not exterminate them or abandon them, for you are a compassionate}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and merciful God.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 32}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?And now, O our God, the God great, mighty, and awe-inspiring, who has kept his covenant and shown loyal love, do not treat lightly all the hardship that has found us, our kings, our princes, our priests, our prophets, our forefathers, and all your people from the days of the kings of Assyria down to this day. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 33}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?You have been righteous in all that has come upon us, for you have acted faithfully; but we are the ones who have acted wickedly. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 34}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?As for our kings, our princes, our priests, and our forefathers, they have not observed your Law nor paid attention to your commandments or to your reminders}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  by which you warned them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 35}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Even when they were in their kingdom and enjoying the abundant goodness that you gave them and they were in the broad and fertile}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  land that you bestowed on them, they did not serve you and did not turn away from their bad practices. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 36}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?So here we are today, slaves\u8212?yes, slaves in the land that you gave to our forefathers to eat its fruitage and its good things. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 37}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Its abundant produce is for the kings whom you have put over us because of our sins. They rule over our bodies and over our livestock as they see fit, and we are in great distress.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 38}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?\u8220?So in view of all this, we are making a binding agreement in writing, and it is attested by the seal of our princes, our Levites, and our priests.\u8221?\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf5\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf7 10\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Those who attested it by putting their seal to it were:\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 Nehemiah the governor,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  the son of Hacaliah,}\line{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 And Zedekiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Maaziah, Bilgai, and Shemaiah; these are the priests.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Also the Levites: Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of Henadad, Kadmiel, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and their brothers Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Hodiah, Bani, and Beninu.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The heads of the people: Parosh, Pahath-moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 26}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Ahijah, Hanan, Anan, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 27}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Malluch, Harim, and Baanah.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 28}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The rest of the people\u8212?the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, the temple servants,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and everyone who separated himself from the peoples of the lands to follow the Law of the true God, along with their wives, their sons, and their daughters, all those with knowledge and understanding}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u8212? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 29}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?joined their brothers, their prominent men, and bound themselves with a curse and an oath, to walk in the Law of the true God, which had been given through Moses the servant of the true God, and to observe carefully all the commandments of Jehovah our Lord, his judgments, and his regulations. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 30}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?We will not give our daughters to the peoples of the land, and we will not take their daughters for our sons.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 31}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?If the peoples of the land bring in their wares and every kind of grain to sell on the Sabbath day, we will not buy anything from them on the Sabbath or on a holy day. We will also forgo the produce of the seventh year and every outstanding debt.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 32}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Also, we imposed the obligation on ourselves for each of us to give a third of a shekel}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  yearly for the service of the house}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  of our God, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 33}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?for the layer bread,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  the regular grain offering, the regular burnt offering of the Sabbaths and the new moons, and for the appointed feasts, for the holy things, for the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and for all the work of the house of our God.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 34}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Also, we cast lots concerning the supply of the wood that the priests, the Levites, and the people should bring to the house of our God by our paternal houses, at the appointed times, year by year, to burn on the altar of Jehovah our God, according to what is written in the Law. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 35}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?We will also bring the first ripe fruits of our land and the first ripe fruits of every sort of fruit tree, year by year, to the house of Jehovah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 36}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?as well as the firstborn of our sons and of our livestock\u8212?according to what is written in the Law\u8212?and the firstborn of our herds and of our flocks. We will bring them to the house of our God, to the priests who minister at the house of our God. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 37}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Also, the firstfruits of our coarse meal, our contributions, the fruitage of every sort of tree, new wine, and oil, we should bring to the priests to the storerooms}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  of the house of our God, along with the tenth}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  from our land to the Levites, for the Levites are the ones who collect the tenths in all our agricultural cities.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 38}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And the priest, the son of Aaron, must be with the Levites when the Levites collect the tenth; and the Levites should offer up a tenth of the tenth to the house of our God, to the rooms}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  of the storehouse. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 39}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?For it is to the storerooms}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  that the Israelites and the sons of the Levites should bring the contribution of the grain, the new wine, and the oil, and that is where the utensils of the sanctuary are, as well as the priests who minister, the gatekeepers, and the singers. We will not neglect the house of our God.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf5\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf7 11\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Now the princes of the people were living in Jerusalem; but the rest of the people cast lots to bring one out of every ten to live in Jerusalem, the holy city, while the other nine stayed in the other cities. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Moreover, the people blessed all the men who volunteered to live in Jerusalem.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And these are the heads of the province}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  who lived in Jerusalem. (The rest of Israel, the priests, the Levites, the temple servants,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  and the sons of the servants of Solomon, lived in the other cities of Judah, each one in his own possession in his city.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Also, there lived in Jerusalem some of the people of Judah and of Benjamin.) Of the people of Judah were Athaiah son of Uzziah son of Zechariah son of Amariah son of Shephatiah son of Mahalalel of the sons of Perez, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and Maaseiah son of Baruch son of Colhozeh son of Hazaiah son of Adaiah son of Joiarib son of Zechariah son of the Shelanite. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?All the sons of Perez who were dwelling in Jerusalem were 468 capable men.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And these were the people of Benjamin: Sallu son of Meshullam son of Joed son of Pedaiah son of Kolaiah son of Maaseiah son of Ithiel son of Jeshaiah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and after him Gabbai and Sallai, 928; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer, and Judah the son of Hassenuah was second in charge of the city.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Of the priests: Jedaiah son of Joiarib, Jachin, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Seraiah son of Hilkiah son of Meshullam son of Zadok son of Meraioth son of Ahitub, a leader of the house}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  of the true God, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and their brothers who did the work of the house, 822; and Adaiah son of Jeroham son of Pelaliah son of Amzi son of Zechariah son of Pashhur son of Malchijah, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and his brothers, heads of paternal houses, 242; and Amashsai son of Azarel son of Ahzai son of Meshillemoth son of Immer, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and their brothers who were mighty, courageous men, 128; and their overseer was Zabdiel, a member of a prominent family.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And of the Levites: Shemaiah son of Hasshub son of Azrikam son of Hashabiah son of Bunni, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and Shabbethai and Jozabad, of the heads of the Levites, who were in charge of the outside business of the house of the true God; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?and Mattaniah, son of Micah son of Zabdi son of Asaph, the conductor of the singing, who led the praises during prayer, and Bakbukiah, the second of his brothers, and Abda son of Shammua son of Galal son of Jeduthun. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?All the Levites in the holy city were 284.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And the gatekeepers were Akkub, Talmon, and their brothers who kept guard in the gates, 172.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The rest of Israel, the priests, and the Levites were in all the other cities of Judah, each in his own inherited property.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The temple servants}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  were living in Ophel, and Ziha and Gishpa were in charge of the temple servants.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?The overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi son of Bani son of Hashabiah son of Mattaniah son of Mica, of the sons of Asaph, the singers; he was in charge of the work of the house of the true God. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?For there was a royal order in their behalf, and there was a fixed provision for the singers as each day required. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?And Pethahiah son of Meshezabel of the sons of Zerah son of Judah was the king\u8217?s adviser}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  for every matter of the people.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?Regarding the settlements with their fields, some of the people of Judah lived in Kiriath-arba and its dependent}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  towns, in Dibon and its dependent towns, in Jekabzeel and its settlements, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 26}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?in Jeshua, in Moladah, in Beth-pelet, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 27}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?in Hazar-shual, in Beer-sheba and its dependent}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  towns, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 28}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?in Ziklag, in Meconah and its dependent}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  towns, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 29}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?in En-rimmon, in Zorah, and in Jarmuth, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf9 30}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 \u160?in Zanoah, in Adullam and their settlements, in Lachish and its fields, and in Azekah and its dependent}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  towns. They settled}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10  from Beer-sheba clear to the Valley of Hinnom.\par}{\